AstAtom *  atom 
)

Forms the bodies that will replace the negation of a given inlined atom.

E.g. a(x) <- (a11(x), a12(x)) ; (a21(x), a22(x)) => !a(x) <- (!a11(x), !a21(x)) ; (!a11(x), !a22(x)) ; ... Essentially, produce every combination (m_1 ^ m_2 ^ ...) where m_i is the negation of a literal in the ith rule of a.

177  }
178 
179  // negations need to be skipped
180  void visitNegation(const AstNegation& cur) override {
181  // add nested atom to black-list
182  ignore.insert(cur.getAtom());
183  }
184 
185  // also skip head if we don't have an inline qualifier
186  void visitClause(const AstClause& clause) override {
187  if (auto clauseHead = clause.getHead()) {
188  auto relation = relCache.getRelation(clauseHead->getQualifiedName());
189  // Only skip the head if the relation ISN'T inline. Keeping the head will ground
190  // any mentioned variables, allowing us to pretend they're grounded.
191  if (!(relation && relation->hasQualifier(RelationQualifier::INLINE))) {
192  ignore.insert(clauseHead);
193  }
194  }
195  }
196 
197  // binary equality relations propagates groundness
198  void visitBinaryConstraint(const AstBinaryConstraint& cur) override {
199  // only target equality
200  if (!isEqConstraint(cur.getOperator())) {
201  return;
202  }
203 
204  // if equal, link right and left side
205  auto lhs = getVar(cur.getLHS());
206  auto rhs = getVar(cur.getRHS());
207 
208  addConstraint(imply(lhs, rhs));
209  addConstraint(imply(rhs, lhs));
210  }
211 
212  // record init nodes
213  void visitRecordInit(const AstRecordInit& init) override {
214  auto cur = getVar(init);
215 
216  std::vector<BoolDisjunctVar> vars;
217 
218  // if record is grounded, so are all its arguments
219  for (const auto& arg : init.getArguments()) {
220  auto arg_var = getVar(arg);
221  addConstraint(imply(cur, arg_var));
222  vars.push_back(arg_var);
223  }
224 
225  // if all arguments are grounded, so is the record
226  addConstraint(imply(vars, cur));
227  }
228 
229  // constants are also sources of grounded values
230  void visitConstant(const AstConstant& c) override {
231  addConstraint(isTrue(getVar(c)));
232  }
233 
234  // aggregators are grounding values
235  void visitAggregator(const AstAggregator& c) override {
236  addConstraint(isTrue(getVar(c)));
237  }
238 
239  // functors with grounded values are grounded values
240  void visitFunctor(const AstFunctor& cur) override {
241  auto fun = getVar(cur);
242  std::vector<BoolDisjunctVar> varArgs;
243  for (const auto& arg : cur.getArguments()) {
244  varArgs.push_back(getVar(arg));
245  }
246  addConstraint(imply(varArgs, fun));
247  }
248 
249  // casts propogate groundedness in and out
250  void visitTypeCast(const AstTypeCast& cast) override {
251  addConstraint(imply(getVar(cast.getValue()), getVar(cast)));
252  }
253  };
254 
255  // run analysis on given clause
256  return Analysis(tu).analyse(clause);
257 }

◆ getInlinedLiteral()

NullableVector< std::vector< AstLiteral * > > souffle::getInlinedLiteral ( AstProgram &  program,
AstLiteral *  lit 
)

Tries to perform a single step of inlining on the given literal.

Returns a pair of nullable vectors (v, w) such that:

  • v is valid if and only if the literal can be directly inlined, whereby it contains the bodies that replace it
  • if v is not valid, then w is valid if and only if the literal cannot be inlined directly, but contains a subargument that can be. In this case, it will contain the versions that will replace it.
  • If both are invalid, then no more inlining can occur on this literal and we are done.

838  // For negations, check the corresponding atom
839  AstAtom* atom = neg->getAtom();
840  NullableVector<std::vector<AstLiteral*>> atomVersions = getInlinedLiteral(program, atom);
841 
842  if (atomVersions.isValid()) {
843  // The atom can be inlined
844  inlined = true;
845 
846  if (atomVersions.getVector().empty()) {
847  // No clauses associated with the atom, so just becomes a true literal
848  addedBodyLiterals.push_back({new AstBooleanConstraint(true)});
849  } else {
850  // Suppose an atom a(x) is inlined and has the following rules:
851  // - a(x) :- a11(x), a12(x).
852  // - a(x) :- a21(x), a22(x).
853  // Then, a(x) <- (a11(x) ^ a12(x)) v (a21(x) ^ a22(x))
854  // => !a(x) <- (!a11(x) v !a12(x)) ^ (!a21(x) v !a22(x))
855  // => !a(x) <- (!a11(x) ^ !a21(x)) v (!a11(x) ^ !a22(x)) v ...
856  // Essentially, produce every combination (m_1 ^ m_2 ^ ...) where m_i is a
857  // negated literal in the ith rule of a.
858  addedBodyLiterals = formNegatedLiterals(program, atom);
859  }
860  }
861  if (atomVersions.isValid()) {
862  for (const auto& curVec : atomVersions.getVector()) {
863  for (auto* cur : curVec) {
864  delete cur;
865  }
866  }
867  }
868  } else if (auto* constraint = dynamic_cast<AstBinaryConstraint*>(lit)) {
869  NullableVector<AstArgument*> lhsVersions = getInlinedArgument(program, constraint->getLHS());
870  if (lhsVersions.isValid()) {
871  changed = true;
872  for (AstArgument* newLhs : lhsVersions.getVector()) {
873  AstLiteral* newLit = new AstBinaryConstraint(constraint->getOperator(),
874  std::unique_ptr<AstArgument>(newLhs), souffle::clone(constraint->getRHS()));
875  versions.push_back(newLit);
876  }
877  } else {
878  NullableVector<AstArgument*> rhsVersions = getInlinedArgument(program, constraint->getRHS());
879  if (rhsVersions.isValid()) {
880  changed = true;
881  for (AstArgument* newRhs : rhsVersions.getVector()) {
882  AstLiteral* newLit = new AstBinaryConstraint(constraint->getOperator(),
883  souffle::clone(constraint->getLHS()), std::unique_ptr<AstArgument>(newRhs));
884  versions.push_back(newLit);
885  }
886  }
887  }
888  }
889 
890  if (changed) {
891  // Not inlined directly but found replacement literals
892  // Rewrite these as single-literal bodies
893  for (AstLiteral* version : versions) {
894  std::vector<AstLiteral*> newBody;
895  newBody.push_back(version);
896  addedBodyLiterals.push_back(newBody);
897  }
898  inlined = true;
899  }
900 
901  if (inlined) {
902  return NullableVector<std::vector<AstLiteral*>>(addedBodyLiterals);
903  } else {
904  return NullableVector<std::vector<AstLiteral*>>();
905  }
906 }

◆ getSipsFunction()

sips_t souffle::getSipsFunction ( const std::string &  sipsChosen)

Returns a SIPS function based on the SIPS option provided.

The SIPS function will return the index of the appropriate atom in a clause given a goal.

E.g. the 'max-bound' SIPS function will return the atom in the clause with the maximum number of bound arguments.

85 
86  // Each SIPS function has a priority metric (e.g. max-bound atoms).
87  // Arguments:
88  // - a vector of atoms to choose from (nullpointers in the vector will be ignored)
89  // - the set of variables bound so far
90  // Returns: the index of the atom maximising the priority metric
91  sips_t getNextAtomSips;
92 
93  if (sipsChosen == "naive") {
94  // Goal: choose the first atom with at least one bound argument, or with no arguments
95  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
96  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
97  const AstAtom* currAtom = atoms[i];
98 
99  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
100  // already processed - move on
101  continue;
102  }
103 
104  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
105  // no arguments
106  return i;
107  }
108

110  // at least one bound argument
111  return i;
112  }
113  }
114

116  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
117  if (atoms[i] != nullptr) {

119  }
120  }
121 
122  // fall back to the first
123  return 0U;
124  };
125  } else if (sipsChosen == "all-bound") {
126  // Goal: prioritise atoms with all arguments bound
127  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
128  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
129  const AstAtom* currAtom = atoms[i];
130 
131  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
132  // already processed - move on
133  continue;
134  }

136  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
137  // no arguments, so all are trivially bound
138  return i;
139  }
140

143  if (numBound == arity) {
144  // all arguments are bound!
145  return i;
146  }
147  }
148 
149  // none found; choose the first non-null
150  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
151  if (atoms[i] != nullptr) {
152  return i;
153  }
154  }
155 
156  // fall back to the first
157  return 0U;
158  };
159  } else if (sipsChosen == "max-bound") {
160  // Goal: choose the atom with the maximum number of bound variables
161  // - exception: propositions should be prioritised
162  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
163  int currMaxBound = -1;

165 
166  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {

168 
169  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
170  // already processed - move on
171  continue;
172  }
173 
174  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
175  // propositions should be prioritised
176  return i;
177  }
178 
179  int numBound = numBoundArguments(currAtom, boundVariables);
180  if (numBound > currMaxBound) {
181  currMaxBound = numBound;
182  currMaxIdx = i;
183  }
184  }
185 
186  return currMaxIdx;
187  };
188  } else if (sipsChosen == "max-ratio") {
189  // Goal: choose the atom with the maximum ratio of bound to unbound
190  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
191  auto isLargerRatio = [&](std::pair<int, int> lhs, std::pair<int, int> rhs) {
192  return (lhs.first * rhs.second > lhs.second * rhs.first);
193  };
194 
195  auto currMaxRatio = std::pair<int, int>(-1, 1); // set to -1
196  unsigned int currMaxIdx = 0U;
197 
198  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
199  const AstAtom* currAtom = atoms[i];
200 
201  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
202  // already processed - move on
203  continue;
204  }
205 
206  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
207  // propositions are as bound as possible
208  return i;
209  }
210 
211  int numBound = numBoundArguments(currAtom, boundVariables);
212  int numArgs = currAtom->getArity();
213  auto currRatio = std::pair<int, int>(numBound, numArgs);
214  if (isLargerRatio(currRatio, currMaxRatio)) {
215  currMaxRatio = currRatio;
216  currMaxIdx = i;
217  }
218  }
219 
220  return currMaxIdx;
221  };
222  } else if (sipsChosen == "least-free") {
223  // Goal: choose the atom with the least number of unbound arguments
224  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
225  int currLeastFree = -1;
226  unsigned int currLeastIdx = 0U;
227 
228  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
229  const AstAtom* currAtom = atoms[i];
230 
231  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
232  // already processed - move on
233  continue;
234  }
235 
236  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
237  // propositions have 0 unbound arguments, which is minimal
238  return i;
239  }
240 
241  int numBound = numBoundArguments(currAtom, boundVariables);
242  int numFree = currAtom->getArity() - numBound;
243  if (currLeastFree == -1 || numFree < currLeastFree) {
244  currLeastFree = numFree;
245  currLeastIdx = i;
246  }
247  }
248 
249  return currLeastIdx;
250  };
251  } else if (sipsChosen == "least-free-vars") {
252  // Goal: choose the atom with the least amount of unbound variables
253  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms, const std::set<std::string>& boundVariables) {
254  int currLeastFree = -1;
255  unsigned int currLeastIdx = 0U;
256 
257  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
258  const AstAtom* currAtom = atoms[i];
259 
260  if (currAtom == nullptr) {
261  // already processed - move on
262  continue;
263  }
264 
265  if (isProposition(currAtom)) {
266  // propositions have 0 unbound variables, which is minimal
267  return i;
268  }
269 
270  // use a set to hold all free variables to avoid double-counting
271  std::set<std::string> freeVars;
272  visitDepthFirst(*currAtom, [&](const AstVariable& var) {
273  if (boundVariables.find(var.getName()) == boundVariables.end()) {
274  freeVars.insert(var.getName());
275  }
276  });
277 
278  int numFreeVars = freeVars.size();
279  if (currLeastFree == -1 || numFreeVars < currLeastFree) {
280  currLeastFree = numFreeVars;
281  currLeastIdx = i;
282  }
283  }
284 
285  return currLeastIdx;
286  };
287  } else {
288  // chosen SIPS is not implemented, so keep the same order
289  // Goal: leftmost atom first
290  getNextAtomSips = [&](std::vector<AstAtom*> atoms,
291  const std::set<std::string>& /* boundVariables */) {
292  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < atoms.size(); i++) {
293  if (atoms[i] == nullptr) {
294  // already processed - move on
295  continue;
296  }
297 
298  return i;
299  }
300 
301  // fall back to the first
302  return 0U;
303  };
304  }
305 
306  return getNextAtomSips;
307 }

◆ isInfixFunctorOp() [1/2]

bool souffle::isInfixFunctorOp ( std::string_view  symbol)

Determines whether a functor should be written using infix notation (e.g.

a + b + c) or prefix notation (e.g. +(a,b,c))

Generally follow Haskell convention: functions w/ symbolic names are infix, otherwise prefix. NOTE: The surface syntax occasionally uses alpha infix operators For backwards compatibility we translate these into symbolic ops.

template<typename To = RamDomain, typename From >
To souffle::ramBitCast ( From  source)

In C++20 there will be a new way to cast between types by reinterpreting bits (std::bit_cast), but as of January 2020 it is not yet supported.

Cast a type by reinterpreting its bits. Domain is restricted to Ram Types only. Template takes two types (second type is never necessary because it can be deduced from the argument) The following always holds For type T and a : T ramBitCast<T>(ramBitCast<RamDomain>(a)) == a

Remaining body literals remain in the same order.
